An Al Jazeera reporter was killed by Israeli army in the West Bank on Wednesday, media reports and the Palestinian Health Ministry have said. According to Al Jazeera, Shireen Abu Akleh was shot while reporting on an army raid in the city of Jenin. The news agency pledged in a statement to prosecute Israel's armed forces and "bring them to justice," while the Israeli military said it was investigating the death of the journalist and could not rule out an attack by Palestinian gunmen.